What can I say, it's a Dunkin' Donuts?  Good coffee, as usual.  Update (1/11/20, not about the business itself, it's still perfectly on point for a Dunkin Donuts): I was walking my (very old, blind, deaf, frequently sickly [with Cushing's, mainly]) cockapoo from my apartment on 18th to Metropolitan Veterinary Clinic on 16th, across the street from this Dunkin Donuts and I'll be darned if a good samaritan purchased a coffee and donut and brought it to the vet with instructions to give it to me.  I appreciated this!!  The past few months with this old dog have been difficult (in November, I thought euthanasia would come before the end of the year) but he's improved significantly (Metro Vet diagnosed an infection that my *prior* vet... seemed to have overlooked) and has at least one more summer in him, hopefully.  I truly appreciated your act of kindness!!

I normally don't do reviews on places because not everyone has the same standard as me or lack thereof, but I have been going to this location every time I work downtown and I get a chance to stop in for the past, approximately, 8 months. The owners are amazingly sweet and they truly take care of their customers. I'll literally walk into the location and she'll already have my coffee on the counter for me and she always remembers to put my hot sauce in the bag for me, I rarely have to ask for it anymore. She's always so welcoming and friendly. It's truly the little things that count and they take care of those little things. I highly recommend anyone to become regulars here, you won't regret it with their dedication.
